69. Trochaic &mearum (Tetrameter Cateleetic), contain· ing seven complete fect, and one that is incomplete. This, next to the iambis senarius, is the commoneat matre in Terence (212 lines in the Andria). Diaeresis generally occurs after the fourth fect, which cannot then be a dactyl. Sometimes the diaeresis comes at the end of the fifth foot, aecompanied by another after the third, or by a caesura in the third. The sevcnth foot is usually a pure trochee, but is sometimes a tribrach. Lines 259 and 260 are thus scanned:—
